Resolves of the Committee of Safety. Whereunto is added the Saints dictionary: or, A catalogue of some pretious books chiefly intended for the use of those that are well-affected to this good new cause. England and Wales. Committee of Safety.
15, [1], 5-25 p.
[s.n.], London, : Printed in the yeare, 1659.
Not in fact by the Committee of Safety, but a satire on what the author perceives as religious irregularity, with particular attention to the Society of Friends. Signatures: A ² A (-A1 and A2) B⁴. Annotation on Thomason copy: "9ber. [i.e. November] 2"; "nouember". Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
